{"title_page": "2019", "text_new": "{{See also|2010s political history}}\n{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Year dab|2019}}\n{{Year nav|2019}}\n{{C21 year in topic}}\n{{Year article header|2019}}\n{{Skip to top and bottom}}\n2019 was designated as International Year of the [[Periodic table|Periodic Table of Chemical Elements]] by the [[United Nations General Assembly]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iupac.org/united-nations-proclaims-international-year-periodic-table-chemical-elements/|title=The United Nations proclaims the international year of the periodic table of chemical elements|website=iupac.org}}</ref> given that it coincides with the 150th anniversary of its creation by [[Dmitri Mendeleev]] in 1869.\n{{TOC limit|2}}\n\n== Events ==\n=== January ===\n* [[January 1]]\n** Unmanned space probe ''[[New Horizons]]'' makes a close approach of the [[Kuiper belt|Kuiper belt object]] (KBO) [[486958 Arrokoth]] at 05:33 UTC.\n** [[Jair Bolsonaro]] begins his four-year term as [[President of Brazil]].\n** [[Qatar]] withdraws from [[OPEC]].\n** Same-sex marriage [[Same-sex marriage in Austria|becomes legal in Austria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.loc.gov/law/foreign-news/article/austria-same-sex-couples-allowed-to-get-married-starting-january-2019/|title=Austria: Same-Sex Couples Allowed to Get Married Starting January 2019|work=[[Library of Congress]]|date=December 12, 2017|accessdate=March 28, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125120112/http://www.loc.gov/law/foreign-news/article/austria-same-sex-couples-allowed-to-get-married-starting-january-2019/|archivedate=January 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[January 3]] \u2013 Chinese probe [[Chang'e 4]] becomes the first human-made object to land on the [[far side of the Moon]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-lands-probe-on-dark-side-of-the-moon-11546493599 |title=China Lands Probe on the 'Dark Side' of the Moon |last=Moss |first=Trefor |date=January 3, 2019 |work