ment de l'ancien ministre Ali Mroudjae est aujourd'hui &#124; Comores Infos|first=La|last=R\u00e9daction|date=May 2, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[May 3]] \u2013 [[Goro Shimura]], Japanese mathematician (b. [[1930]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.math.princeton.edu/news/professor-emeritus-goro-shimura-1930-2019|title=Professor Emeritus Goro Shimura 1930\u20142019 &#124; Math|website=www.math.princeton.edu}}</ref>\n* [[May 5]] \u2013 [[Norma Miller]], American dancer, actress and author (b. [[1919]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/06/obituaries/norma-miller-dead.html|title=Norma Miller, Lindy-Hopping 'Queen of Swing,' Is Dead at 99|first=Robert D.|last=McFadden|date=May 6, 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n* [[May 6]]\n** [[John Lukacs]], Hungarian-American historian (b. [[1924]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.news.yahoo.com/john-lukacs-iconoclastic-historian-dead-95-150932265.html|title=John Lukacs, iconoclastic historian, dead at 95|website=uk.news.yahoo.com}}</ref>\n** [[Seymour Nurse]], Barbadian cricketer (b. [[1933]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://caribbeannewsservice.com/now/legendary-former-west-indies-batsman-seymour-nurse-dies/|title=Legendary former West Indies batsman Seymour Nurse dies &#124; Caribbean News Service|first=C. N. S.|last=Editor|website=caribbeannewsservice.com}}</ref>\n* [[May 7]] \u2013 [[Jean Vanier]], Canadian Catholic philosopher (b. [[1928]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.larche.org/en/web/guest/news/-/asset_publisher/mQsRZspJMdBy/content/passing-away-of-jean-vanier|title=Passing away of Jean Vanier - News - L'Arche internationale|website=www.larche.org}}</ref>\n* [[May 8]]\n**[[Sprent Dabwido]], 13th [[President of Nauru]] (b. [[1972]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/former-nauru-president-sprent-dabwido-dies-aged-46|title=Former Nauru president Sprent Dabwido dies aged 46|website=SBS News}}</ref>\n** [[Yevgeny Krylatov]], Soviet and Russian composer (b. [[1934]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/culture/new