t to Saudi Arabia and [[United Arab Emirates]] following the [[2019 Abqaiq\u2013Khurais attack|September 14 attack]] on Saudi oil refineries.<ref>{{citation|website=Sky News|date=Sep 21, 2019|accessdate=Sep 21, 2019|title=Trump approves deployment of US forces in Saudi Arabia|author=Sharon Marris |url=https://news.sky.com/story/trump-approves-deployment-of-us-forces-in-saudi-arabia-11815482}}</ref><ref>{{citation|website=India Today |date=Sep 21, 2019|accessdate=Sep 21, 2019|title=Donald Trump to send troops to Saudi Arabia, hold off on striking Iran |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/world/story/donald-trump-approves-deployment-of-us-forces-to-saudi-arabia-uae-1601522-2019-09-21}}</ref> Both Saudi Arabia and [[Iran]] vow to defend themselves.<ref>{{citation|website=Sky News|date=Sep 21, 2019|accessdate=Sep 21, 2019|title=Saudi foreign minister says his country will defend itself against Iranian threats|url=https://news.sky.com/story/saudi-foreign-minister-says-his-country-will-defend-itself-against-iranian-threats-11816188|author=Mark Stone}}</ref>\n* [[September 22]] \u2013 Nearly three weeks after [[Effects of Hurricane Dorian in The Bahamas|Hurricane Dorian]] makes landfall on [[The Bahamas]], the official death toll stands at 52 and 1,300 are reported missing. Rescuers report the widespread stench of rotting bodies in the rubble.<ref>{{citation|website=CNN|date=September 22, 2019 |accessdate=Sep 22, 2019|author1=Rosa Flores|author2=Holly Yan|title=In this crippled part of the Bahamas, US medics can smell more bodies than they can find|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/09/22/americas/east-grand-bahama-us-medics-and-survivor/index.html}}</ref>\n<!--U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and Indian Prime minister [[Narendra Modi]] address 50,000 [[Indian Americans]] at the ''Howdy, Modi: Shared Dreams Bright Feature'' rally in [[NRG Stadium]] in Houston, Texas.<ref>{{citation|website=Politico|date=Sep 22, 2019|accessdate=September 22, 2019 |author=ANITA KUMAR|title=At a rally like no other, Trump woos Indian American voters ahead of 2020 |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/09/22/trump-indian-american-voters-2020-1507266}}</ref>-->\n* [[September 23]]\n** One of the largest and oldest travel firms, [[Thomas Cook Group|Thomas Cook]], goes bankrupt as last-minute rescue negotiations fail, stranding 600,000 tourists worldwide.<ref>{{citation|website=The New York Times|date=Sep 23, 2019|title=How Could Travel Giant Thomas Cook Fail? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/23/travel/why-thomas-cook-travel-collapsed.html}}</ref>\n** Russia formally adopts the [[Paris Agreement|Paris climate agreement]].<ref>{{citation|website=Euractiv|title=Russia formally joins Paris climate pact |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/climate-environment/news/russia-formally-joins-paris-climate-pact/|date=Sep 23, 2019|accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[September 24]]\n** The [[Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] [[R (Miller) v The Prime Minister|unanimously rules]] that the [[2019 British prorogation controversy|September 2019 prorogation of Parliament]] was unlawful and void.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49810261 |title=Supreme Court: Suspending Parliament was unlawful, judges rule |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=September 24, 2019 |accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n** The [[Supreme Court of Spain]] unanimously rules in favour of the exhumation of the remains of Spanish dictator [[Francisco Franco]] from the [[Valle de los Ca\u00eddos]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Franco exhumation: Spain's Supreme Court backs move to cemetery|publisher=BBC news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49807372|date=September 24, 2019|accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref> He was finally exhumed on 24 October, being re-inhumed in a private crypt with his wife.<ref>{{cite news|title=Controversial exhumation of Franco's takes place in Spain|publisher=CNN|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/10/24/europe/franco-exhumation-spain-intl/index.