i capital kills at least 78 at rush hour|author=ABDI GULED|date=Dec 28, 2019 |url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/police-car-bomb-somalias-capital-kills-67954666?cid=clicksource_76_null_articleroll_hed}}</ref>\n* [[December 29]]\n** A report by the Multi-Sector Epidemic Response Committee (CMRE) indicates that 2,231 people have died so far in the [[Kivu Ebola epidemic|2018\u201320 Kivu Ebola epidemic]] in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.<ref>{{cite web|website=AFP / MSN Noticias|title=\u00c9bola mat\u00f3 a 2.231 personas en RDC desde agosto de 2018|language=es|trans-title=Ebola has killed 2,231 people in DRC since August 2018|date=Dec 29, 2019 |url=https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/virales/%c3%a9bola-mat%c3%b3-a-2231-personas-en-rdc-desde-agosto-de-2018/ar-BBYrbpM}}</ref>\n** The [[Taliban]]'s ruling council agrees to a temporary cease-fire in Afghanistan, opening a door to a peace agreement with the United States.<ref>[https://www.politico.com/news/2019/12/29/taliban-council-agrees-cease-fire-afghanistan-090398 Taliban council agrees to cease-fire in Afghanistan] Politico, Dec 29,2019</ref>\n* [[December 30]] &ndash; Chinese authorities announce that [[He Jiankui]], who claimed to have created the world's [[Lulu and Nana controversy|first genetically edited human babies]], has been sentenced to three years in prison and fined 3&nbsp;million yuan (US$430,000) for his genetic research efforts.<ref name=\"NYT-20191230\">{{cite news |last=Wee |first=Sui-Lee |title=Chinese Scientist Who Genetically Edited Babies Gets 3 Years in Prison - He Jiankui's work was also carried out on a third infant, according to China's state media, in a new disclosure that is likely to add to the global uproar over such experiments. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/30/business/china-scientist-genetic-baby-prison.html |date=30 December 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=30 December 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"CNN-20191230\">{{cite web |last1=Yee |first1=Isaac